BT /F2 10 Tf 50 744 Td () Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 730 Td (| Command | What it does | Typical use |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 716 Td (| --- | --- | --- |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 702 Td (| `scan` | Scans one target page or a discovered local target; supports browser-assisted login and `--profile` presets | Quick vulnerability check |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 688 Td (| `crawl` | Crawls in-scope links across multiple pages; supports browser-assisted login and `--profile` presets | Broader site sweep |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 674 Td (| `report` | Re-renders or previews a saved report | Review an existing JSON, Markdown, or HTML report |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 660 Td (| `audit` | Shows the append-only audit trail | Review scans and fix events |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 646 Td (| `baseline` | Saves a scan snapshot for later comparison | Track a known-good state |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 632 Td (| `compare` | Compares two saved scans and crawl coverage | See what changed |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 618 Td (| `drift` | Compares saved reports and highlights baseline drift | Watch for scan, file, log, and config changes |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 604 Td (| `secrets` | Scans files for obvious secret exposure | Check logs and configs for leaked values |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 590 Td (| `vuln scan` | Inventories local software versions and matches a small bundled offline advisory ruleset | Start a vulnerability-scanner workflow without changing the system |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 576 Td (| `bundle` | Packages a report and related artifacts into a ZIP archive | Share a handoff bundle |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 562 Td (| `doctor` | Checks the local machine and app environment | Health check without a URL |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 548 Td (| `server-check` | Discovers the server layout and scans the local app target | VPS/server discovery mode |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 534 Td (| `incident` | Detects suspicious activity in logs and can apply a denylist or fail2ban snippet | Defensive incident response |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 520 Td (| `watch` | Monitors logs, file drift, and process activity in a snapshot or follow loop; writes reports under `outputs/` by default and can compare file drift against `--baseline` | Continuous defensive monitoring |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 506 Td (| `timeline` | Shows the chronological order of findings and containment actions | Saved incident report replay |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 492 Td (| `integrity` | Compares monitored files against a saved baseline | File integrity drift monitoring |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 478 Td (| `fix --local` | Applies the first real local edit lane | Backup, edit, validate, rollback if needed |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 464 Td (| `demo` | Runs the local demo site | Test target for development |) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 450 Td (| `demo-site` | Compatibility alias for the local demo site | Legacy command support |) Tj ET
