stream
BT /F1 13 Tf 50 744 Td (Safety Principles) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 724 Td () Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 710 Td (- Report-only findings stay read-only.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 696 Td (- Safe fixes must be reversible.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 682 Td (- Every fix plan must include rollback metadata.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 668 Td (- Approval is required for anything outside the allowed fix level.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 654 Td (- Secrets must never be printed into reports or logs.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 640 Td (- The executor is the only module that can perform changes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 626 Td (- All other modules produce findings, plans, or recommendations only.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 612 Td (- The first live-edit lane is `fix --local`, and it only touches a discovered server) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 598 Td (  file after backup and validation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 584 Td (- The incident-response lane is `incident`, and it only writes a denylist include after) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 570 Td (  analysis and confirmation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 556 Td (- The watch lane is `watch`, and it stays log-only in v1: it observes, scores, and) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 542 Td (  recommends containment without auto-blocking.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 528 Td () Tj ET
BT /F1 13 Tf 50 514 Td (Working Agreement) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 494 Td () Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 480 Td (These rules govern how we build PsyberShield together:) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 466 Td () Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 452 Td (1. Comments should be short working notes, not tutorial prose.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 438 Td (2. If a comment is needed, keep it close to the code and make it practical.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 424 Td (3. Use comments for the lines that need a nudge, not for everything.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 410 Td (4. Prefer code that reads clearly without a lot of explanation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 396 Td (5. Function names should read naturally to a human.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 382 Td (6. If a function name is unclear, ask before creating it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 368 Td (7. When asking about a function name, explain its purpose first so the naming choice) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 354 Td (is easy to review.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 340 Td (8. Every file we create should be actively used and connected to the rest of the app.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 326 Td (9. Do not create placeholder functions that live in isolation or force a file to exist) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 312 Td (without purpose.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 298 Td (10. Prefer small, related files that each earn their place in the project.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 284 Td () Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 270 Td (Comment style examples:) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 256 Td () Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 242 Td (- Good: `# normalize input`) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 228 Td (- Good: `# check v1 headers`) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 214 Td (- Bad: `# We normalize the input first so the rest of the scan can trust one canonical) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 200 Td (  URL.`) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 186 Td (- Bad: `# We focus on a short list of headers that are easy to verify and easy to) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 172 Td (  explain to users.`) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 50 158 Td () Tj ET
endstream
endobj
